metadata.name: Painterly #50
metadata.description:
A generative abstract involving a particle system that represents a roll of paint being smudged onto the canvas. Additional stylization using long, black strokes leaves one with the impression of a pond or marsh. Enjoy this token being created as the "paint" flows and pulls itself up and down the canvas.

Pressing the Space Bar while the token is rendering will allow the output to render indefinitely.  Otherwise, the output will stop at a set point to produce a static image.  

The output is produced in either portrait or landscape orientation.

Press the Down Arrow to save any frame as a 1990x1080 or 1080x1990 PNG.
Click or tap the canvas to toggle full screen mode.
Press the Space Bar during rendering to activate dynamic output mode.

Created using p5.js.

metadata.name: Landscapes in my mind #74
metadata.description:
In this work I tried to convey the idea of a landscape (many landscapes) with hills, trees, grass, bushes, skies and clouds. As is normal on fxhash I have accomplished all this by writing the code that generates the elements in a scene.
While writing the code to obtain these landscapes I did not try to reproduce landscapes seen in reality or in photography, rather I followed from time to time ideas of landscapes that came to my mind as a sort of lucid dream. I hope I managed to convey this idea of a landscape that is halfway between reality and fantasy.

Lands and Clouds are rendered using a mix of simplex noise and FBM (Fractional Brownian Motion), trees are generated with recursive functions an placed using Poisson Disk Sampling distribution. The distribution density could be homogeneous (land heightmap drive the density) or biased to have more density towards the top, bottom, left or right of the land.


Developed with p5.js using WEBGL renderer.
Rendering is faster with chrome browser.

[1] to render at 1600x1600
[2] to render at 2400x2400
[3] to render at 3200x3200
[s] to save a png at last rendered resolution.


Features:
"LandPalette": 20 colormaps
"TreePalette": 20 colormaps
"Light":  Morning, Evening, Night
"SkyColor": Blue, Azure, Turquoise, Gray, VioletRed
"Haze": True, False
"Rainbow":  True, False
"Grayscale": True, False
"TreeDensity": Homogeneous, Top, Bottom, Left, Right


Created by Andrea Belloni, fxhash: anbello, twitter: @Waterflowing0. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: Prospettive Astratte - Floating structures #17
metadata.description:
Perspective and abstraction, generates 3D a structure, a grid of floating objects projected in perspective, in some cases a close up detail. Sometime close to a regular pattern, sometime more chaotic like any urban development. 
Inside complex generated textures, based on a colored palette tanke from a Leonardo Da Vinci and Botticelli painting

By either MOUSE CLICKING over the canvas or touching it, color palette will redistribute over the *same* token shape, as well transparency will be affected. This could give the effect of a changing shape, while instead are hidden shapes "re-emerging" from transparency, while other may disappear.

metadata.name: Sequoias #19
metadata.description:
High in the hills and mountains of the Pacific Northwest‚Äôs coastal ranges reside the treasured Giant Sequoias (Sequoiadendron giganteum) ‚Äì colossal creatures whose lives are measured in millenia.  These conifers can reach upward an astonishing 85 meters (on average), live 4,000 years, and weigh in at a mind-bending 6,000 tons. 

‚ÄúSequoias‚Äù is an impression of ancient majesty and natural beauty‚Äìa tribute to the uniqueness and solitude of these stunning lifeforms.  In this work, a generative sky brightens the smokey, distant hills created generatively in an impressionistic style.  Two or more Giants Sequoias sprout limbs like wings spreading out to take flight into the sky they reach toward.  Created in a more illustrative style, the contrast is intended to make the subjects seem surreal in the presence of the ordinary.  As an animated generative system, collectors can witness the curiosity of capriciously twisting branches and thoughtfully generated foliage as ‚ÄúSequoias‚Äù builds the features of each tree.  A constrained color palette showcases the features of the subject with complimentary variety to complete this wonderfully designed artwork.

Each of the 25 available editions are HD 1990x1080 and can be saved locally with the DOWN ARROW after the output has fully generated.  

Selling Price is Dutch-Auction Based:

Opening Bid: 10 Tezzos each.
5 Tezzos after 30 minutes.
2.5 Tezzos after 60 minutes.
1 Tezzos after 90 minutes.
Unminted editions will be burned at the end of the next market cycle (within 72 hours).

Published 22, February 2022 on the fxhash Marketplace.
Created by Ed Cavett using p5.js and adapted derivatives of the p5.js Example Library with additional coding procedures created by Ed Cavett.

Standard Rendering Duration: Setup: 10-12 seconds; Full-render: 30-35 seconds.
Key Generative Components: array flow fields with p5.js noise-waves factored to position, and stochastic prn randomness.

metadata.name: Circles In A Square World #126
metadata.description:
Circles In A Square World, is a play on the saying "being square", usually referring to someone who is more conventional and boring. In the society I grew up in, being square is what people are being pushed towards. A traditional 9 - 5 in a well paying office job the goal. But I believe that in a world where the majority is square, living the circle life is way more fulfilling.

For each square in Circles In A Square World there is a small chance a circle will be drawn instead. The series re-uses the palettes that were discovered in Ode to Color as well. 

To watch the drawing process press 'd'.

To get a higher resolution for printing add ?size=4096 at the end of the URL in the live view (you can use any size you want).

metadata.name: Physarum Logo #408
metadata.description:
These past few months have been a great experience and with the beta ending, I wanted to create a piece to thank all collectors and pay tribute to this great platform. 

The piece is based on a physarum simulation with a couple of tweaks, such as continuous behavioural changes and an extra information layer that further manipulates the physarum.

There are ~262k particles simulated in parallel, so it is quite GPU heavy. 

Each piece features one of 12 different colour pallets, the text and a couple of cell-like bodies running around the screen.

Controls: 
S - Save image
H - Hide Text
Click/Touch - Spawn particles

Disclaimer: This is nothing official by the platform itself, merely a tribute by an artist and fan. 

With all that said: Thank you to everyone, and see you in 1.0 !
